INSERT INTO public.news_articles (slug, title, category, excerpt, content, featured, published, published_at, meta_title, meta_description, keywords, og_image_url, author_name) VALUES ('talitrix-highlights-247365-command-center-the-backbone-of-its-operations', 'Talitrix Highlights 24/7/365 Command Center: The Backbone of Its Operations', 'Announcement', $tksobdxq3$Talitrix is highlighting the capabilities of its 24/7/365 Command Center, which provides continuous monitoring and operational support for agencies and participants using Talitrix electronic monitoring technology.$tksobdxq3$, $tmj0jbeue$Talitrix is highlighting the capabilities of its 24/7/365 Command Center, which provides continuous monitoring and operational support for agencies and participants using Talitrix electronic monitoring technology.

Staffed around the clock, including nights, weekends, and holidays, the Command Center is operated by real, trained monitoring specialists who actively oversee device activity, manage alerts, respond to agency requests, and provide support to program participants by answering calls, addressing questions about equipment or program requirements, and helping resolve technical issues.

“Our industry doesn’t operate on a 9-to-5 schedule,” said Justin Hawkins, Chief Executive Officer at Talitrix. “Our Command Center reflects that reality. Whether it’s a routine check-in, participant support, or a critical alert, our trained team is always available to respond.”

Key functions of the Talitrix Command Center include:

• 24/7/365 Monitoring: Continuous oversight of monitoring programs to ensure alerts and activity are reviewed at all hours.

• Holiday and After-Hours Coverage: Support remains available nights, weekends, and holidays when agencies may have limited staffing.

• Agency Communication: The Command Center answers incoming calls and provides operational support to supervising agencies.

• Participant Support: Staff help monitored individuals understand and comply with bond or release conditions, while also providing guidance on billing, equipment, troubleshooting, and overall program support.

• Alert Management: Monitoring specialists review and triage alerts generated by monitoring devices and escalate when necessary.

By combining Talitrix’s technology with trained personnel, the Command Center strengthens program oversight, enhances participant support, and ensures that every monitoring operation runs smoothly, truly serving as the backbone of Talitrix’s operations.

About Talitrix

Talitrix develops advanced monitoring technology for public safety agencies across the United States. Through innovative hardware, intelligent software, and a focus on officer and community safety, Talitrix delivers solutions that strengthen accountability and modernize supervision.$tmj0jbeue$, true, true, '2026-04-01T16:42:33.946Z', 'Talitrix Highlights 24/7/365 Command Center: The Backbone of Its Operations', 'Talitrix is highlighting the capabilities of its 24/7/365 Command Center, which provides continuous monitoring and operational support for agencies and particip', NULL, '/news-images/talitrix-highlights-247365-command-center-the-backbone-of-its-operations.png', 'Madelyn Hawkins');
INSERT INTO public.news_articles (slug, title, category, excerpt, content, featured, published, published_at, meta_title, meta_description, keywords, og_image_url, author_name) VALUES ('talitrix-commends-douglas-county-for-continued-dedication-to-public-safety', 'Talitrix Commends Douglas County for Continued Dedication to Public Safety', 'Announcement', $tmqhs4ot9$Alpharetta, GA – November 7, 2025 - Talitrix commends the Douglas County Sheriff’s Office and the Douglas County District Attorney’s Office for their efforts in apprehending a recent subject under investigation. Their continued pursuit of justice, particularly in cases involving child predators, demonstrates a continued commitment to protecting the citizens and children of Douglas County.$tmqhs4ot9$, $t0aemewa9$Alpharetta, GA – November 7, 2025 - Talitrix commends the Douglas County Sheriff’s Office and the Douglas County District Attorney’s Office for their efforts in apprehending a recent subject under investigation. Their continued pursuit of justice, particularly in cases involving child predators, demonstrates a continued commitment to protecting the citizens and children of Douglas County.

In light of recent monitoring requests, Talitrix recognizes the critical role electronic monitoring plays in supporting community safety. The company remains committed to assisting Douglas County officials in ensuring individuals under court supervision are properly monitored through advanced technology and responsive service.

“I want to recognize the Douglas County Sheriff’s Office and the Douglas County District Attorney’s Office for the work they do each day to keep citizens safe from dangerous offenders,” said Micah Gravley, Chief of External Affairs at Talitrix. “We are honored to work alongside our partners in Douglas County to provide reliable solutions that help protect citizens.”

Talitrix is also dedicated to protecting lives affected by sexual and violent crimes and proudly offers the Talitrix Shield App, a free, downloadable app providing sexual and domestic violence survivors with real-time protection and peace of mind.

Further information is available in FOX 5 Atlanta’s report, “Prosecutors fight bond for man facing 14 child sex exploitation counts.” Click here to read the full article.

About Talitrix
 Talitrix is a leading provider of advanced electronic monitoring solutions designed to enhance accountability, improve efficiency, and promote public safety. Headquartered in Alpharetta, Georgia, Talitrix partners with law enforcement and judicial agencies nationwide to deliver innovative tools that support effective supervision and rehabilitation.

Media Contact: communications@talitrix.com$t0aemewa9$, false, true, '2025-11-07T18:42:34.761Z', 'Talitrix Commends Douglas County for Continued Dedication to Public Safety', 'Alpharetta, GA – November 7, 2025 - Talitrix commends the Douglas County Sheriff’s Office and the Douglas County District Attorney’s Office for their efforts in', NULL, '/news-images/talitrix-commends-douglas-county-for-continued-dedication-to-public-safety.jpg', 'Madelyn Hawkins');
INSERT INTO public.news_articles (slug, title, category, excerpt, content, featured, published, published_at, meta_title, meta_description, keywords, og_image_url, author_name) VALUES ('talitrix-and-sc-monitoring-services-announce-partnership-to-bring-first-sled-approved-gps-wrist-wearable-to-south-carolina', 'Talitrix and SC Monitoring Services Announce Partnership to Bring First SLED-Approved GPS Wrist Wearable to South Carolina', 'Announcement', $tqpoqy6n0$Alpharetta, GA/Columbia, SC – October 28, 2025 Talitrix, a national leader in independent GPS wristband monitoring, is proud to announce that its T-Band, the first wrist wearable of its kind, has been officially approved by the South Carolina Law Enforcement Division (SLED). This milestone comes through Talitrix’s partnership with SC Monitoring Services, a trusted South Carolina-based provider of electronic monitoring solutions.$tqpoqy6n0$, $tpr9otm0n$Alpharetta, GA/Columbia, SC – October 28, 2025 Talitrix, a national leader in independent GPS wristband monitoring, is proud to announce that its T-Band, the first wrist wearable of its kind, has been officially approved by the South Carolina Law Enforcement Division (SLED). This milestone comes through Talitrix’s partnership with SC Monitoring Services, a trusted South Carolina-based provider of electronic monitoring solutions.

Earning SLED approval represents a major milestone, opening the door to new partnerships with state, county, and municipal agencies dedicated to improving accountability, safety, and rehabilitation through innovative technology.

“This approval marks a tremendous step forward in our mission to transform community supervision through innovation, enhanced security, and human-centered design,” said Justin Hawkins, CEO of Talitrix. “We are honored to have our T-Band approved by SLED and to partner with SC Monitoring Services, whose leadership will be paramount in bringing the most comprehensive, secure, and human-focused solution suite to South Carolina.”

Amber Gutierrez, President of SC Monitoring Services, added: “SC Monitoring Services is honored to serve as the exclusive provider of Talitrix’s advanced GPS technology in South Carolina. This partnership reflects our shared commitment to public safety, innovation, and dignity for the individuals we serve. We look forward to bringing this state-of-the-art solution to the state’s courts, sheriffs, and communities.”

Together, Talitrix and SC Monitoring Services are bringing advanced GPS monitoring technology to law enforcement and correctional agencies across the state, combining innovation with local expertise and full-service support.

About Talitrix

Talitrix, the global leader in GPS wrist wearable technology, is transforming the justice system through innovation and accountability. Our industry’s first wrist-wearable GPS monitoring device delivers real-time behavioral analytics designed to improve compliance, reduce stigma, and enhance public safety. Its platform is trusted by law enforcement, courts, corrections, and community supervision programs nationwide. With a strong foundation in integrity, innovation, and social responsibility, Talitrix remains committed to safer communities and brighter futures.

About SC Monitoring Services

SC Monitoring Services, LLC is a woman-owned, South Carolina-based company dedicated to enhancing public safety through innovative and reliable electronic monitoring solutions. Founded to support the judicial system and reduce incarceration costs, the company offers state-of-the-art wrist-worn GPS technology through an exclusive partnership with Talitrix. SC Monitoring Services provides a full-service approach that includes 24/7 customer support, real-time system access for agencies, and a secure victim notification app. With a strong local presence and commitment to compliance with state standards, the company serves as a trusted partner in pretrial supervision, house arrest, and alternative sentencing programs across South Carolina.$tpr9otm0n$, false, true, '2025-10-28T19:05:41.676Z', 'Talitrix and SC Monitoring Services Announce Partnership to Bring First SLED-Approved GPS Wrist Wearable to South Caroli', 'Alpharetta, GA/Columbia, SC – October 28, 2025 Talitrix, a national leader in independent GPS wristband monitoring, is proud to announce that its T-Band, the fi', NULL, '/news-images/talitrix-and-sc-monitoring-services-announce-partnership-to-bring-first-sled-approved-gps-wrist-wearable-to-south-carolina.jpg', 'Madelyn Hawkins');
INSERT INTO public.news_articles (slug, title, category, excerpt, content, featured, published, published_at, meta_title, meta_description, keywords, og_image_url, author_name) VALUES ('talitrix-recognizes-domestic-violence-awareness-month-with-continued-support-for-victims-through-the-talitrix-shield-app', 'Talitrix Recognizes Domestic Violence Awareness Month with Continued Support for Victims Through the Talitrix Shield App', 'Announcement', $t3a26710y$Alpharetta, GA – October 9, 2025 – Domestic violence impacts lives every day across the United States and around the world. Over one in three women and one in four men in the U.S. will experience some form of domestic violence in their lifetime. This October, during Domestic Violence Awareness Month, Talitrix reaffirms its commitment to protecting survivors through innovative technology and life-saving resources.$t3a26710y$, $tl07ktdeh$Alpharetta, GA – October 9, 2025 – Domestic violence impacts lives every day across the United States and around the world. Over one in three women and one in four men in the U.S. will experience some form of domestic violence in their lifetime. This October, during Domestic Violence Awareness Month, Talitrix reaffirms its commitment to protecting survivors through innovative technology and life-saving resources.

Talitrix’s top priority is saving and protecting lives. In support of domestic violence survivors, the company is proud to offer the Talitrix Shield App—a free, downloadable app designed to empower victims of domestic violence with real-time protection and peace of mind.

The Shield App allows users to geo-fence key locations in their daily lives—including home, work, school, medical offices, and shopping areas. The exclusive Floating Buffer Zone technology enables victims to move freely while ensuring they are notified if a participant wearing a Talitrix band enters their proximity. Both the victim and the participant receive notifications, helping to prevent dangerous encounters before they occur.

“Our purpose is simple but profound: to save lives and restore hope through second chances. Every decision we make begins and ends with public safety and the victims we serve,” said Justin Hawkins, Chief Executive Officer at Talitrix. “We believe accountability and compassion can coexist—that technology, when used with integrity, can change the course of a life and strengthen entire communities. Behind every data point is a person, a family, and a future worth protecting.”

Key Features of the Talitrix Shield App:

• Floating Buffer Zone – Active geofencing for safety without restricting the victim’s movement.

• Real-Time Notifications – Instant alerts if a monitored participant approaches.

• Free Download – Available on personal smartphones at no cost to users.

The Talitrix Shield App also features a quick-dial safety feature, allowing users to easily contact 911, the 24/7 Talitrix Call Center, or the supervisor of the participant on the Talitrix monitor.

For those seeking immediate help, the National Domestic Violence Hotline provides confidential, 24/7 support. Resources are available at thehotline.org or by calling 1-800-799-SAFE (7233).

About Talitrix
 Talitrix is a leader in wearable GPS technology and behavioral monitoring, providing innovative solutions to enhance public safety and protect individuals. With a strong foundation in integrity and social responsibility, Talitrix remains committed to safer communities and brighter futures.

Media Contact

communications@talitrix.com$tl07ktdeh$, false, true, '2025-10-09T17:50:03.263Z', 'Talitrix Recognizes Domestic Violence Awareness Month with Continued Support for Victims Through the Talitrix Shield App', 'Alpharetta, GA – October 9, 2025 – Domestic violence impacts lives every day across the United States and around the world. Over one in three women and one in f', NULL, '/news-images/talitrix-recognizes-domestic-violence-awareness-month-with-continued-support-for-victims-through-the-talitrix-shield-app.png', 'Madelyn Hawkins');
INSERT INTO public.news_articles (slug, title, category, excerpt, content, featured, published, published_at, meta_title, meta_description, keywords, og_image_url, author_name) VALUES ('ohow6x0lensyc0db1d6ryr6kxwdymn', 'Talitrix Strengthens Presence in Louisiana with Multiple State Contracts and Growth throughout Parishes Statewide', 'Announcement', $tbgvz3fy1$ALPHARETTA, GA – October 9, 2025 - Talitrix, creator of the industry’s-first independent GPS wrist wearable in criminal justice, announced its expansion into Louisiana with two major state contracts. In addition, Talitrix is now working with over 12 parishes across the state, furthering its mission to enhance public safety, streamline operations for law enforcement agencies, and support positive outcomes for individuals in the Louisiana justice system.$tbgvz3fy1$, $t9evv9gsn$ALPHARETTA, GA – October 9, 2025 - Talitrix, creator of the industry’s-first independent GPS wrist wearable in criminal justice, announced its expansion into Louisiana with two major state contracts. In addition, Talitrix is now working with over 12 parishes across the state, furthering its mission to enhance public safety, streamline operations for law enforcement agencies, and support positive outcomes for individuals in the Louisiana justice system.

By combining wearable technology with a data-driven platform, Talitrix provides real-time GPS tracking, behavioral analytics, and robust reporting tools that give Louisiana law enforcement and community supervision officers a clearer picture of compliance. These insights not only improve accountability but also help agencies allocate resources more effectively, reduce administrative burdens, and focus on reducing recidivism.

“We are excited about our partnership with Louisiana and look forward to working with state and local leaders to meet the electronic monitoring needs for their communities,” said Micah Gravley, Chief External Affairs Officer at Talitrix. “This is the start of a long-term commitment to supporting public safety and rehabilitation efforts across the state.”

This latest expansion marks another step in Talitrix’s growing national footprint. Already serving jurisdictions across 32 states, Talitrix has earned a reputation as a trusted partner for law enforcement, courts, and corrections agencies. In addition to its GPS wrist technology, Talitrix provides a 24/7 call center, customizable alerts, and scalable reporting systems. These tools are all designed to improve efficiency within the criminal justice system.

“Our Talitrix team is devoted to making a difference in Louisiana and nationwide,” Gravley stated. “Every contract we sign represents more than growth—it represents lives impacted, agencies supported, and communities made safer.”

About Talitrix

Talitrix, the global leader in GPS wrist wearable technology, is transforming the justice system through innovation and accountability. Our industry first wrist-wearable GPS monitoring device delivers real-time behavioral analytics designed to improve compliance, reduce stigma, and enhance public safety. Its platform is trusted by law enforcement, courts, corrections, and community supervision programs nationwide. With a strong foundation in integrity, innovation, and social responsibility, Talitrix remains committed to safer communities and brighter futures.

Talitrix Media Contact:

Micah Gravley: micah@talitrix.com

Madelyn Oliver: madelyn@talitrix.com$t9evv9gsn$, false, true, '2025-10-09T17:39:41.089Z', 'Talitrix Strengthens Presence in Louisiana with Multiple State Contracts and Growth throughout Parishes Statewide', 'ALPHARETTA, GA – October 9, 2025 - Talitrix, creator of the industry’s-first independent GPS wrist wearable in criminal justice, announced its expansion into Lo', NULL, '/news-images/ohow6x0lensyc0db1d6ryr6kxwdymn.jpg', 'Carter Jarrett');